      "title": "Clear fractions, get standard form",
      "content": "Multiply $\\dfrac{1}{cx} = \\dfrac{x}{84} + \\dfrac{1}{c}$ through by $84cx$: $84 = cx^2 + 84x$ -> $cx^2 + 84x - 84 = 0$."
    },
    {
      "title": "One solution -> discriminant = 0",
      "content": "$b^2 - 4ac = 0$: $84^2 - 4(c)(-84) = 0$ -> $7056 + 336c = 0$ -> $c = -21$."
    },
    {
      "title": "Answer",
      "content": "The value $c=-21$ satisfies the one-solution condition, so <strong>-21</strong> is correct."
    }
  ]
